This paper discusses the development of an environment for co-developing text and ontological description, which is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The use of literate programming suggests a focus on natural language processing (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG), while the development of the Karyotype Ontology suggests a focus on bioinformatics (cs.DB) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges of combining free text and ontologies, which could be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR).
